track_notes:
This track starts at the National Trust car park (Â£4/day for non-members). This is a short walk down the hill from Nantmor halt on the Welsh Highland Railway.

Pass under the railway - do not attempt to follow the route across the tracks shown on old maps! Pass the buddles where copper ore was ground. Follow the path up the valley. You will pass pylons that once carried an aerial rope-way for the mine, and several adits. The mine has some deadly drops, so do not explore too far!

Keep straight on until the stile at the top of the pass. Cross it and bear right. Follow the narrow track. Some scrambling is required. Ignore the next stile. Cross at the one after and proceed to the summit.

A recently-strengthened fence provides good antenna support.
This is an alternative approach from the north, starting beside Llyn Dinas. It joins my other track from Cwm Bychan.

Includes a short scramble from Bwlch-y-Sygyn to Grib Ddu - not for the faint hearted....G4TJC route from Llyn Dinas is much more straight forward which is the way we returned to Beddgelert - on a well maintained stepped path.
